law.history: Repealed 1952 Ky. Acts ch. 134, sec. 63, effective June 19, 1952. -- Repealed in part 1946 Ky. Acts ch. 54, sec. 1. -- Recodified 1942 Ky. Acts ch. 208, sec. 1, effective October 1, 1942, from Ky. Stat. sec. 1486bb-12.

metadata.catchline-at-repeal: Purgation by county clerk outside cities of first class, on grounds of death, disqualification or failure to vote.
